Only one prior hand on record (a hero fold). No usable villain reads yet. With pocket fives facing a limp, raising is the standard play — build the pot with an equity advantage and deny free cards.

Raising to **6** (3× the big blind) — a standard heads-up iso-raise size.

{"action": "raise", "amount": 6}

Villain has shown **zero aggression** across all streets in 9 hands — aggr_turn: 0, aggr_flop: 0, aggr_river: 0. This is their first bet in any street, on a J-T-8-6 board (heavily connected). That break in pattern is a major red flag — when a passive player suddenly bets, they almost always have it.

I hold only AKd (overcards) — just 6 outs (~13% on the river). Pot odds require ~31% equity to call profitably (8 to call into 26). I'm far short of that threshold against a range that's heavily weighted toward made hands (straights, two pair, sets). 

